Lucapa Diamond and its partners have announced the results from the latest sale of diamonds from the Lulo alluvial diamond mine in Angola, Sociedade Mineira Do Lulo (SML). Read more about Lucapa Diamond Company A total of 4,269 carats of Lulo diamonds sold for gross proceeds of US$6.6 million on a 100% basis, representing an average price of US$1,550/carat. Sales year to date amounts to US$28.0 million (A$40.1 million) from 20,397 carats at US$1,371/carat.